---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="work at the Learning Lab -- elisa diop-weyer">
  <article class="ll">
    <header>
      <h1 class="title">work at the Learning Lab</h1>
      <p class="meta">updated 26 october 2025</p>
    </header>

    <p class="lede">highlights</p>

    <section>
      <h2 class="course">TS 280 -- python notebooks</h2>
      <p>
        developed a suite of notebooks, including simple chat completions with
        GPT + ElevenLabs API to input a text, choose a target language, and
        output audio in that language -- alongside more conceptual notebooks:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <span class="u">ping-pong:</span> repeatedly translating from language a
          to language b and tracking the convergence of the translation;
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="u">telephone:</span> translating from language a to b to c
          to d and then to the target language, evaluating how the intermediary
          translations impact the output;
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="u">thematic focus + iteration</span> -- built with a
          professional translator to mimic his process: a first set of
          completions creates "context" strings focused on cultural context,
          authorship, and etymology; those strings + the original text are passed
          through a completion that returns a structured output with the
          translation and its strengths and weaknesses. context + the three
          outputs are then iterated, so completion <em>t</em> corrects the
          weakness of completion <em>t&minus;1</em>. the final translation is
          compared to a canonical, human translation. final output = final
          translation + json of strengths/weaknesses of each intermediate
          translation + comparison to the canonical.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="course">GENED 1196 -- python notebooks</h2>
      <p>
        prototyped an "AI-proof" oral assignment. generated visuals (tarot cards
        with imagery + titles tied to core concepts, approaches, and case
        studies); prototyped a next.js file using the OpenAI realtime API to
        stream audio from student responses and generate follow-up questions
        live. a selection mechanism produced an initial series of follow-ups, a
        "judge" picked the top three, and a RAG chat completion over the syllabus
        + rubric chose what most needed elaboration based on the top follow-ups
        and the course material.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="course">MUSIC 250HFA -- python notebooks</h2>
      <p>
        developed a suite of notebooks using librosa and matplotlib to visualize
        musical snippets with 2D and 3D spectrograms, and to compare audio across
        different covers of the same song -- e.g. visualizing how far different
        musicians emphasize different syllables in the same lyric.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="course">MOD HEB 241R -- python notebook</h2>
      <p>
        built a notebook using OpenAI chat completions with structured outputs
        and OpenAI's Whisper API to help students edit videos. the notebook took
        a prompt -- e.g. "discussions of environmental policy" -- and output a cut
        of every snippet where the video matched the prompt.
      </p>
    </section>

    <p class="back"><a href="/portfolio">← portfolio</a></p>
  </article>
</Base>

